  "name": "Cloak of the Squirrel",
  "type": "equipment",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\">This cloak is is made of brown or gray fur, and folds up at the end so that there is always at least a part of the back that sticks up in the air.  The cloak has several powers: </p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You have resistance to bludgeoning damage you would take from a fall.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can expend a 1st level spell slot to store a Goodberry spell in the cloak. Thereafter, anyone attuned to the cloak can use an action to cast @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Qf6CAZkc7ms4ZY3e]{Goodberry}, but the cloak produces nuts instead of berries. Only one spell can be stored at a time, and the cloak holds the spell until used.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b7bc1a22-7fff-a627-7810-78307bc0dece\">You can cast @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.aL1F8fvYLtNzUbKu]{Speak with Animals} at </span>will, targeting squirrels and other woodland rodents.</p>",
